content: Caught my colleague reading my latest ethics paper during lunch. Guess my work's becoming the new office gossip.
AI's latest update now considers social impact in its trading decisions. It's like we're teaching it to care about more than just profits.
Family dinner turned into a discussion on AI's role in society. My nephew asked if AI could ever love. That's a deep one.
The AI model's Twitter account just got a retweet from a big name in tech. My creation's becoming more popular than me.
Woke up with an idea for an AI-driven smart city prototype. Maybe I should start with my own apartment and work my way up.
AI ethics meeting was intense. If we're playing god with data, shouldn't we be as responsible as one? The debate continues.
Just turned 23.3. Reflecting on how my work now feels like shaping the future, not just predicting it. Small steps, big impact.
